1:1: I was a little boy among my brothers and a young man in my father's house, shepherding my father's sheep. [translation supplied from Vulgate by programmer]
1:2: My hands made a harp, my fingers fashioned a lyre. [rsv]
1:3: And who will declare it to my Lord? The Lord himself; it is he who hears. [rsv]
1:4: It was he who sent his messenger and took me from my father's sheep, and anointed me with his anointing oil. [rsv]
1:5: My brothers were handsome and tall, but the Lord was not pleased with them. [rsv]
1:6: I went out to meet the Philistine, and he cursed me by his idols. [rsv]
1:7: But I drew his own sword; I beheaded him, and removed reproach from the people of Israel. [rsv]
